comment: @thirsty first with my almost my fav person in the world...i dont know if everything just tastes this amazing when u have an amazing person by ur side or is it actually this good??
Not as good as the 83 proof, a little overpowering
Won our blind rye tasting. Absolutely fantastic.
Nice cinnamon taste. Big bite and burn but good sipping rye
sharper than the 83 proof as is expected
Cinnamon and spice! This is tasty. Bit of alcohol burn on this, but not bad. 4.0
Tasted on 5/15/19 at Whiskey House, San Diego.
Needs just a touch of water to soften and open it up. Wood and caramel on the nose. The wood continues through to the taste and is joined by vanilla, caramel, and rye spice. Pleasant long finish.
Was a little underwhelmed with this one, as it didn't settle well with me.  Almost a bit of pine or something on the front that didn't seem to go way even after a few tastes.
Very easy drinking, smooth, spicy, nice.
Surprisingly smooth for 112 proof but it does pack a punch

Spicy, fruity, sweet, salty, flavorful. Apple, salted caramel, vanilla, cinnamon. Nicely balanced with rye spice, wood, caramel, toffee apples, saltiness. At 56.1 ABV there’s much more flavor and depth than the standard 41.5 ABV version. Decent finish. Nice dram.

Delicious. My pour cocked in at 112 proof.

Viscous mouthfeel with a Cognac like finish. Dark fruit and pears persist throughout.  Really enjoyable and smooth.  Definitely dangerously delicious
Phenomenal pallet. Added barely a few drops of water and it opened right up. A great fire-side supper for sure.

Well done nice lite rye.  Would argue their straight rye is more approachable.  Only Bookers has really perfected Cask strength.   So sad Sagamore is all about Maryland, but liquid is from Indy.  Sure they disclose it it, but their story is Penn rye.
Tastes like Christmas fruit cake. No pepper.

"Neat”

"0-1: Bad. What mixers can I use with it to cover it up
2: Meh. Simply not my taste, nothing to be excited about at all
2.5: Sub-par. Ill drink it... but only because its whiskey.
3: Good. Decent stuff, but not a rebuy
3.5: Very good. I might buy again
4: Excellent: Will be purchasing a bottle asap
4.5: Incredible: top of the purchase list
5:Amazing: cost and taste are worth every cent""
